00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:05,759
The video features

67
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:10,740
Professor Isao Imai's "Fluid Mechanics (Volume 1)" textbook

68
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:17,460
This book was first published in 1973 and is still being reprinted as a masterpiece

69
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:23,880
There's also an e-book version, so you can have it without taking up shelf space

70
00:05:25,259 --> 00:05:29,279
But this book has a big mystery

71
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:35,760
The title says "Volume 1" but Volume 2 doesn't exist

72
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:42,020
Professor Imai passed away without ever writing Volume 2

73
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,760
But there's something even more mysterious

74
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:51,960
This first volume contains the table of contents for the non-existent second volume

75
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,460
Look at this

76
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:59,519
Volume 2 doesn't exist, yet there's a clear outline of what was planned

77
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,900
Only the table of contents remains

78
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:08,900
Boundary layers, turbulence, magnetohydrodynamics

79
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,000
Various topics are listed

80
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:13,220
I want to read about all of them...

81
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,960
But there's no Volume 2

82
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:20,100
Yet it's still being published as "Volume 1"

83
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,200
Some readers say

84
00:06:22,810 --> 00:06:25,340
